Interface Classifier

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    Format
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractFormat, JSON

    public interface Classifier
    A class that can classify sequences from a reader. With just a simple gate method (for the caller).
    Since:
    31-Mar-2020
    Version:
    0.1.3
    Author:
    lsafer

      • classify

        <T> Clazz<T> classify(ClassifyToken<T> token)
               throws java.io.IOException
        Set the ClassifyToken.output on the given token to the proper clazz for the text in the ClassifyToken.input.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the component-type of the clazz returned
        Parameters:
        token - the classifying instance that holds the variables of this classification
        Returns:
        the proper clazz for the text in the given reader
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if any I/O exception occurs
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the given 'token' is null
        ClassifyException - if any classifying exception occurs
